</section><section data-mw-section-id="44" id="mwA8k"><h3 id="Music">Music</h3>
<ul id="mwA8o"><li id="mwA8s">West German pop band <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Dschinghis_Khan" title="Dschinghis Khan" id="mwA8w">Dschinghis Khan</a> took its name from the German-language spelling of Genghis Khan, "Dschingis Khan". They participated in the <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Eurovision_Song_Contest_1979" title="Eurovision Song Contest 1979" id="mwA80">Eurovision Song Contest 1979</a> with <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Dschinghis_Khan_(song)" title="Dschinghis Khan (song)" id="mwA84">their song of the same name</a>.</li>
<li id="mwA88">The artist <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Miike_Snow" title="Miike Snow" id="mwA9A">Miike Snow</a> released the song "<a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Genghis_Khan_(Miike_Snow_song)" title="Genghis Khan (Miike Snow song)" id="mwA9E">Genghis Khan</a>" in 2017.</li></ul>

