5" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwBTQ"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-15" id="cite_note-15"><a href="./Genghis_Khan#cite_ref-15" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-15" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation web" about="#mwt27" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"title":{"wt":"The World&apos;s Richest Terror Army"},"url":{"wt":"http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p02rhxgr"},"publisher":{"wt":"BBC"},"author1":{"wt":"Peter Taylor"},"authorlink1":{"wt":"Peter Taylor (journalist)"},"date":{"wt":"May 27, 2015"},"quote":{"wt":"Beheadings and mass slaughter are the hallmark of [[Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant|IS]] – whole villages massacred, women cast into slavery. But this butchery is not random. It is callous and calculated, as former British intelligence officer [[Alastair Crooke]] points out: &apos;They in fact in some ways copy Genghis Khan and the Mongol approach to military conquest. You create an absolute fear deliberately in your enemies, and the first time you come to a village you kill everyone, the dogs, the cats, everything. Destroy it down to the ground.&apos;"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBTU"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Peter_Taylor_(journalist)" title="Peter Taylor (journalist)" id="mwBTY">Peter Taylor</a> (May 27, 2015). <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p02rhxgr" id="mwBTc">"The World's Richest Terror Army"</a>. BBC. <q id="mwBTg">Beheadings and mass slaughter are the hallmark of <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Islamic_State_of_Iraq_and_the_Levant" title="Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant" id="mwBTk">IS</a> – whole villages massacred, women cast into slavery. But this butchery is not random. It is callous and calculated, as former B