3" class="mw-reference-text">Page 246-248, Validation by Holiness or Sovereignty: Religious Toleration as Political Theology in the Mongol World Empire of the Thirteenth Century, Christopher P. Atwood, The International History Review, Vol.26, No.2 (June 2004), <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://globalmiddleages.org/sites/default/files/pdf-files/atwood.pdf" id="mwBbo">here</a></span></li><li about="#cite_note-Juvayni-44" id="cite_note-Juvayni-44"><span rel="mw:referencedBy"><a href="./Genghis_Khan#cite_ref-Juvayni_44-0"><span class="mw-linkback-text">1 </span></a><a href="./Genghis_Khan#cite_ref-Juvayni_44-1"><span class="mw-linkback-text">2 </span></a></span> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-Juvayni-44" class="mw-reference-text">"<a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://faculty.washington.edu/modelski/CAWC.htm" id="mwBbs">Central Asian world cities</a> <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120118121401/https://faculty.washington.edu/modelski/CAWC.htm" about="#mwt139" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"webarchive ","href":"./Template:Webarchive"},"params":{"url":{"wt":"https://web.archive.org/web/20120118121401/https://faculty.washington.edu/modelski/CAWC.htm"},"date":{"wt":"January 18, 2012"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBbw">Archived</a><span about="#mwt139" id="mwBb0"> January 18, 2012, at the </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Wayback_Machine" title="Wayback Machine" about="#mwt139" id="mwBb4">Wayback Machine</a><link rel="mw:PageProp/Category" href="./Category:Webarchive_template_wayback_links" about="#mwt139" id="mwBb8"/>", University of Washington.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-Morgan-45" id="cite_note-Morgan-45"><a href="./Genghis_Khan#cite_ref-Morgan_45-0" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-Morgan-45" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt143" typeof="m